added.title: Looking For Love
added.description: When they receive an alert that Love is missing, the Titans set out to find her using musical clues.

added.title: The Chaff
added.description: In an effort to get Teen Titan Go! canceled, Control Freak shows off some deleted scenes.

added.title: Them Soviet Boys
added.description: In order to quickly get through their chores and karate lessons, the Titans learn how to montage

added.title: Little Elvis
added.description: The Titans team up with Shazam in order to defeat the evil Mr. Mind.

added.title: The Spinoffs
added.description: Wishing to get rid of Gumball once and for all, his nemesis Rob offers up a variety of reality, action and comedy shows featuring characters other than Gumball. Unfortunately for Rob, each one is worse than the last.

added.title: The Transformation
added.description: Penny's family is unhappy that she's decided to come out of her shell literally. And Penny wants her family to come out of their shells...also literally. They are at an impasse so who do they turn to in their time of trouble? Gumball of course! Needless to say he is way outside of his comfort zone.

added.title: The Understanding
added.description: Gumball and Darwin find themselves in serious trouble when they agree to everything the new kid in school says. The truth is they can't understand a word that he says. Peter Pepperoni has been home schooled and developed a very odd way of speaking. Due to a series of misunderstandings Gumball and Darwin end up on the run from the law.

added.title: The Ad
added.description: To make ends meet, the Wattersons are forced to rent out their house. However, with nowhere else to stay they decide to secretly remain at the house. When they accidentally surprise their guests, an elderly pair of fainting goats, they faint...unsurprisingly.  The Wattersons fear the worst and attempt to cover up this "accident".

added.title: The Ghouls
added.description: It's Halloween in Elmore. As the kids go trick or treating we see what everyone in town is up to. The ghosts and ghouls are finding it increasingly difficult to scare children, and are only scaring part-time. Can Gumball and Darwin help them get their scare back?

added.title: Fan or Foe
added.description: When Elder Con comes to the Creek, Craig, Kelsey and JP each have a con experience they'll never forget.

added.title: New Jersey
added.description: After donning a brand new Jersey, JP is recruited by the Hockey Kids! The only way to get JP back is for Craig and Kelsey to hit the ice!

added.title: The Sunflower
added.description: Our Trio makes a new friend in the Creek, but when her pet befalls a tragic fate, Kelsey believes she knows how to help.

added.title: Craig World
added.description: Craig creates an amusement park in the Creek! But when things start to get stale, he vows to make it bigger and better, no matter what it takes!

added.title: Body Swap
added.description: Fed up with their home experiences, Craig, Kelsey and JP agree to switch bodies!

added.title: Excalibear
added.description: On the Bears' visit to a medieval vegetable-village, Grizz starts to believe that he's the rightful king.

added.title: Meat House
added.description: The Bears and their new friend Squatter Otter attempt to live in mysterious house made of meat.

added.title: Pirate Parrot Polly
added.description: On their quest for hidden treasure, the Bears team up with Polly the Parrot Pirate.

added.title: Baby Bear Genius
added.description: Ice Bear receives an invitation to attend a prestigious school for baby geniuses… but Grizz and Panda do not.

added.title: Bug City Sleuths
added.description: To survive in a city inhabited by bugs, the Bears become noir-style detectives.

added.title: Total Trauma Rama
added.description: Duncan, normally the bad kid, has an identity crisis when his pranks start curing people of their fears.

added.title: The Doomed Ballooned Marooned
added.description: After over-decorating a birthday table with balloons several kids float away to a deserted island.

added.title: Legends of the Paul
added.description: Duncan grows jealous of Paul's 100 year time out and determined to be King of the Pranks, has to team up with Paul, learn his ways, then double-cross and become a legend.

added.title: A Bridgette Too Far
added.description: As season three draws to a close, Bridgette becomes desperate to star in an episode.

added.title: Venthalla
added.description: Owen has his super ball confiscated and locked up in Chef's office. Duncan, seeing an opportunity to get help escaping the daycare, leads an away team into the vents to recover Owen's ball.

added.title: Onionless
added.description: Onion needs to leave town so Apple has to survive the weekend alone while taking care of Onion's beloved plant.

added.title: Party Popper
added.description: Apple and Onion's party plans are interrupted by a grumpy guest.

added.title: Face Your Fears
added.description: Apple and Onion must face their fears if they are to save French Fry from their bad advice.

added.title: Apple's Short
added.description: Apple wants to experience love.

added.title: Positive Attitude Theory
added.description: Apple and Onion spend a day in Falafel's shoes and use their positive attitude to prove he shouldn't be so grumpy.

added.title: The Question
added.description: Steven shows some city slicker gems how the cowboys lived.

added.title: Made of Honor
added.description: Steven has a big surprise for the Crystal Gems.

added.title: Reunited
added.description: Steven brings everyone together for a special reunion.

added.title: Legs from Here to Homeworld
added.description: Steven travels to visit family.

added.title: Familiar
added.description: With many changes going on in his life, Steven tries to find his place in the world.

added.title: This One Goes to 11
added.description: During one last stop by a toy store before Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max's maiden voyage across the Atlantic, Ben runs into an old bully, Kevin 11, who now has new powers. He's able to transform into aliens just like Ben, such as the bootleg doppelganger of Cannonbolt. Wreckingbolt!

added.title: Rath of Con
added.description: Back stateside, Ben can't get into a cat cosplay competition, Top Tail, without a costume of his own; but when he goes Rath, a new cat-like alien with an attitude, Ben's newfound wild side quickly becomes much more than he bargained for.

added.title: Poles Apart
added.description: A trip to the South Pole goes upside down when Team Tennyson lands on the North Pole instead, but Ben quickly discovers the culprits: Solar & Polar Twain, magnetically-powered scientists who want to hold the world ransom by threatening to reverse Earth's magnetic poles!

added.title: Show Don't Tell
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max arrive at a Native American national park to witness the Ayasha Plinths, an ancient Stonehenge-like rock formation. But when the sinister sorcerer Hex arrives, Ben must battle against a beast Hex magically made out of huge rocks!

added.title: Welcome to Zombozo-Zone!
added.description: During medieval times, Team Tennyson must fight to remember that they're not in the past at all, but actually at a Renaissance-esque faire, where "King Zombozo" has hypnotized its guests into thinking they live in the past!

added.title: Showdown Part I
added.description: The Faction infiltrates Galvan in an attempt to destroy Azmuth.  (Introducing new Nemetrix aliens Omnivoracious & Vicetopus.)

added.title: Showdown Part 2
added.description: Ben must deal with a past failure while a deranged Malware launches his final attack on Azmuth.

added.title: Tummy Trouble
added.description: When the Incursean armada kidnaps the Gourmand Queen, Ben and Rook must get the warring Gormand factions to work together to save her and stop the Incursean invasion.

added.title: Vilgax Must Croak
added.description: Ben and Rook escort Vilgax to a maximum-security prison planet, but the Incurseans have other plans. (Introducing Eighteight.)

added.title: While You Were Away
added.description: Dr. Psychobos and Princess Attea have invaded Rook's home planet Revonnah with an army of Incurseans! (Introducing new Ben alien, Astrodactyl.)

added.title: The Frogs of War Part 1
added.description: The Incursean Armada, with the help of Dr. Psychobos, have invaded the Earth. (Reintroducing old Ben alien, BenMummy.)

added.title: The Frogs of War Part 2
added.description: With Ben missing, the Incurseans now control the Earth. It's up to Rook and the remaining Plumbers to lead the resistance and fight back! (Introducing new Ben alien, Bullfrag.)

added.title: Rules of Engagement
added.description: Princess Looma returns to claim Ben as her husband, and she's not going to let anyone stand in her way!  (Featuring Julie and Ship.)

added.title: Rad
added.description: With Plumber agents trapped in Incursean territory, Ben and Rook must employ the services of Rad Dudesman, the roughest, toughest smuggler in the galaxy.  (Introducing Rad Dudesman, return of classic Ben alien, Eye Guy.)

added.title: Evil's Encore
added.description: Dr. Animo reminisces about when he once took control of the Plumber's HQ in Mount Rushmore. (Flashback episode.)

added.title: Video Date
added.description: Panda is an avid e-dater, and when a lovely French woman matches with him and agrees to a video chat date. Panda and his brothers engineer the situation so Panda is able to show the best side of himself on the video chat, even if that side of him is completely exaggerated.

added.title: Pet Shop
added.description: Pet Shop tells the tale of where the Baby Bears once lived, and after a run-in with a video crew shooting a Sarah McLachlan-type animal adoption video, almost seized an opportunity to find a home separated from each other.

added.title: Chloe and Ice Bear
added.description: On a day out with just Ice Bear, Chloe realizes Ice Bear only runs errands for his brothers. Determined to show him a fun day in the city, Chloe promises to help Ice Bear have a good time, even if it means staying  in a museum after it closes.

added.title: Cupcake Job
added.description: When the Bears' beloved laptop breaks, they finally have the need to do something they've never done before: get jobs. Working at a trendy cupcake shop, the Bears find  that the working world is much tougher than they realized.

added.title: Hibernation
added.description: The bears, being an urban bunch, hadn't ever heard of the idea of hibernation until Chloe tells them about it. Grizz, loving the idea of eating a ton and then just sleeping to his heart's content, goes for it with reckless abandon.  But Grizz is so excited for hibernating... that he can't fall asleep.

added.title: Hot to the Touch
added.description: Finn goes on a quest to prove Flame Princess isn't really evil.

added.title: Jake vs. Me-Mow
added.description: Finn and Jake grapple with a tiny feline assassin.

added.title: The New Frontier
added.description: When Jake has a dream that predicts when his last days are, Finn intervenes when the events of the dream start to actually happen.

added.title: Incendium
added.description: Jake sets Finn up with the Flame Princess with fiery results.

added.title: Marceline's Closet
added.description: Finn and Jake spend a nerve-wracking afternoon trapped in Marceline's closet.

added.title: Picking Up Margaret
added.description: Mordecai wants to give Margaret a ride to the airport.

added.title: K.I.L.I.T. Radio
added.description: Muscle Man wants a local radio station to play the song he wrote for Starla.

added.title: Carter and Briggs
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby enter a donut contest to win a cameo on their favorite cop show.

added.title: Skips' Stress
added.description: Skips has to lower his stress before it kills him.

added.title: Cool Cubed
added.description: The guys need to unfreeze Thomas' brain after he chugs a slushy.

added.title: Unikitty News!
added.description: You're watching the Unikingdom News Show Super Good Morning Time Program Action Information Show, a variety news program put on (badly) by Unikitty and the gang: Hawkodile does the weather, Puppycorn does sports despite knowing none of the rules, Dr. Fox puts on a fun science-y cooking segment that goes awry, and Richard wants this to stop. Unikitty's got some hard hitting reporting and a big scoop after the break, if the studio survives that long!

added.title: Dinner Apart-y
added.description: Unikitty and Puppycorn are invited to Master Frown and Brock's apartment for a dinner party. But the two roommates are butting heads, and are anything but on the same page. Can Unikitty help Brock and Master Frown get back in harmony before the dinner party is ruined? Will Puppycorn figure out which door is the bathroom?

added.title: R & Arr
added.description: It's Lazy Sunday, and Unikitty and Puppycorn are having such an amazing time hanging out on the couch, they never want to move! Richard insists they have chores to do, but they're unwilling to let Lazy Sunday end. The two go to ridiculous lengths to never leave the comfort of their sofa, rowing it across the castle and like a ship and conscripting their friends to abandon their chores and join Lazy Sunday… no matter how dangerous and impossible it might become!

added.title: License to Punch
added.description: Hawkodile's caught by the Action Police for bodyguarding without an Action License. He's can't protect the kingdom or do anything rad until he does, but the test at the DMV (The Department of Mayhem and Violence) is for nerds! Forced to retire his gloves, Hawkodile struggles to live a life without punching, so Unikitty vows to help her friend contain his urge to be action-y and study for the test. But there's more to the test than meets the eye.

added.title: Buggin' Out
added.description: When Unikitty and the gang discover a gross bug in the castle, they desperately want it gone for good, but Unikitty refuses to allow them to squish it, no matter how icky or dangerous looking it is. What sort of web is Unikitty weaving for her friends?

added.title: Sun Scream/City of Frownsville
added.description: Sun Scream: The girls get the ultimate sunburn and must try to fight crime despite their UV damage./The City of Frownsville: When the tearful Lou Gubrious sets a crying ray on Townsville, the girls must find a way to stop the tears before the town is flooded.

added.title: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs/Mizzen in Action
added.description: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs: The girls must literally work as one to try and stop Mojo from destroying Townsville./Mizzen in Action: Captain Crack McGraigen and his crew are tossed forward in time where discover the chemical X that marks the spot and it is up to the girls and Professor to send the super-charged pirates back to their own time.

added.title: That's Not My Baby/Simian Says
added.description: That's Not My Baby!: The girls save a baby from a monster attacking Townsville but can't find the mother. Can these three superheroes manage to take care of one little baby?/Simian Says: When the Narrator is mysteriously bound and gagged, Mojo Jojo takes over his job, ordering the girls to steal for him all around Townsville.

added.title: West in Pieces
added.description: It's the old west and Mojo the Kid has robbed the first bank ever and forced the sheriff out of town and it is up to the Steamypuff Girls to save the day at a high-noon showdown.

added.title: Aspirations
added.description: The Gangreen Gang is actually committing brilliant crimes. But behind every great gang, there has to be a great woman.

added.title: Lights Out!
added.description: When Bliss brings a new tech product to town, it's more powerful than imagined.

added.title: Bucketboy!
added.description: When the girls tell Barry he's a hero, he takes it too far.

added.title: The Fog
added.description: A new villain arrives in Townsville and gives the old villains an enticing offer.

added.title: The Spoon
added.description: A crash landing sends Townsville over the edge.

added.title: Cat Burglar
added.description: An alarmingly familiar cat burglar terrorizes Townsville.

added.title: Merry Moochmas
added.description: It's wintertime in Aberdale and Clarence is convinced his winter wish for snow in Arizona will come true! However, his classmate Belson along with his grumpy cousin Gary Mooch are a little tougher to convince.

added.title: Pizza Hero
added.description: It's the end of the school year, and as is tradition at Aberdale Elementary, Papa Marianio is slated to dish out his famous pizza along with a spectacle of song and dance. As the kids wait in excitement, they share memories about times with Papa.

added.title: Sumo Goes West
added.description: Clarence learns his best friend Sumo may transfer to another school! It's up to Clarence to protest, petition and rally to convince everyone to let Sumo stay - or face losing his closest school pal!

added.title: Valentimes
added.description: When Clarence notices his teacher Ms. Baker is the only one in class left without a Valentine this year, he decides to enlist the help of Sumo to set her up with Sumo's teacher, Mr. Mozer! Will sparks fly or will the boy's naive view of romance backfire?

added.title: Clarence for President
added.description: It's school election time at Aberdale Elementary, and Jeff is once again determined to become Class President. However like previous years, he's unsuccessful in connecting with other kid. That is until he sees a shoe-in puppet President, the lovable Clarence!

added.title: RV Olympics
added.description: Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus compete in the RV Olympics.

added.title: Uncle Melvins
added.description: Legendary rock band, the Melvins, team up with Uncle Grandpa to help a young girl who wants to win her school's talent show.

added.title: Uncle Baseball
added.description: A failing little league team on the brink of giving up gets help from Uncle Grandpa and some Major League Baseball players.

added.title: Costume Crisis
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes improvements to a kid's Halloween costume.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Runs for President
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve run against one another in the RV presidential race.

added.title: Trial By Mino
added.description: Separated from the others, Kai and Zane discover a party of Geckles who suspect them of being in league with the Skull Sorcerer, and bring them before their leader, Chancellor Gulch, who subjects them to a "Trial-By-Mino."

added.title: The Skull Sorcerer
added.description: Separated from the others, Cole must trust his instincts and make the right choices to find his way to the surface to alert King Vangelis of the dangerous Skull Sorcerer.

added.title: The Real Fall!
added.description: An entire episode chronicles the ninja's most bizarre adventure yet: in which Cole, Princess Vania and Master Wu fall down a seemingly endless tunnel, into the bowels of Shintaro Mountain.

added.title: Dungeon Party
added.description: Having survived their fall into the mountain, Cole, Wu and Princess Vania befriend a motley group of survivors, called the Lowly, and are told the story of how they too ended up at "Rock-Bottom."

added.title: Dungeon Crawl!
added.description: Having joined forces with the Lowly in their quest to defeat King Vangelis, Cole, Wu, and Vania have to find a way out of the bottom of the mountain, a place said to be inescapable.

added.title: The Lady and the Queen/The AB's Silver Screen Debut
added.description: The Lady and the Queen: China Riot finds a new Bakugan: Barbetra. But this buzzy new Bakugan is a bit timid on the battleground. Riot takes her on as her new project to turn her into the battle queen she knows she can be./The AB's Silver Screen Debut: Lord Brakken and Duran have teamed up and are now the Bakugan film business. They look to the Awesome Brawlers for their expertise in both Bakugan culture and film making to get their movie made!

added.title: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!/Magnus
added.description: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing./Magnus: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League/The Ancient Elder
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League: Benton Dusk is in the process of renovating a state of the art Bakugan Brawling stadium. When it comes to brawling, who better to test out the new arena than the Awesome Brawlers!/The Ancient Elder: Dan finds a new baku-bud in Gillitar. Well "bud" may be too strong a word, Dan and gang quickly learn that Gillator has a few "quirks" that keep him from fitting in with the rest of the Awesome Brawler's Bakugan.

added.title: Bakugan Wynton/The Boy from Brazil
added.description: Bakugan Wynton: Wynton has a new device that tracks down Bakugan! Right out of the gate the device works and, Wynton meets: Batrix. Like his name, Batrix is a little batty, and these two are certainly in for a "batty" first adventure./The Boy from Brazil: The Awesome Brawlers are off to a soccer match! In the process of doing so Shun discovers a new Bakugan friend, the boisterous Ramparian, and a new foe in Brazilian soccer star: Pepe.

added.title: Haunted House/Two of a Kind
added.description: Haunted House: Rumor has it that there's a haunted building in Los Volmos, and the Awesome Brawlers are on the case! Who doesn't like a good ghost hunt, plus capturing a ghost on camera should make Awesome Brawlers' next video a huge success!/Two of a Kind: Veronica Venegas is doing a special report on the Awesome brawlers own: Lightening! The special report takes a back seat when Lightening is challenged to a brawl. Lightening uses this brawl the perfect opportunity to rollout his new Bakugan partner: Tretorous.

added.title: Play Date
added.description: Toyman takes over the Justice League and turns them into avatars in a diabolical video game.

added.title: Repulse!
added.description: Luthor infects Superman with a magnetic charge that repels everything. As the repulsing charge grows, the Magnetized Man of Steel is fated to spend the rest of his life isolated in space unless the Justice League can figure out a way to free him.

added.title: Trick or Threat
added.description: Four kids in Justice League costumes are trick or treating on Halloween when they investigate a spooky house. As dangers befalls them inside, they come to realize that maybe they're not kids at all, but real Justice Leaguers under a spell.

added.title: Speed Demon
added.description: Batman has to enlist the help of Jason Blood, aka the Demon, when Brother Blood turns the Batmobile into a sentient, demonic entity.

added.title: Hat Trick
added.description: When Felix Faust steals Zatanna's magical top hat, the Justice League must help retrieve it before the evil wizard can use it to create a magic portal, releasing the demon Ghast.

added.title: Historias Alternas
added.description: Rob crea una variedad de programas y formatos derivados ambientados en Elmore para reemplazar a Gumball.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Transformacion
added.description: iLe piden a Gumball que resuelva una disputa entre Penny y su familia!
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Comprension
added.description: Gumball y Darwin se meten en problemas al tener un malentendido con un chico nuevo en la escuela.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Anuncio
added.description: Los Watterson se ven obligados a alquilar su casa a un par de cabras ancianas que se desmayan.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Los Espectros
added.description: Halloween ya no es lo que solía ser. ¿Pueden Gumball y Darwin ayudar a los monstruos a recuperar su capacidad de asustar?
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La pregunta
added.description: Steven les muestra a unas gemas citadinas cómo vivían los vaqueros.

added.title: Dama de honor
added.description: Steven tiene una gran sorpresa para las Gemas de Cristal.

added.title: Reunificados
added.description: Steven reúne a todos para un evento especial.

added.title: Piernas del Planeta Madre
added.description: Steven viaja para visitar a su familia.

added.title: La burla
added.description: En un esfuerzo por cancelar "Los Jóvenes Titanes en Acción", Control Fenómeno muestra algunas escenas eliminadas del programa.

added.title: Familiar
added.description: Con tantos cambios en su vida, Steven intenta encontrar su lugar en el mundo.

added.title: Los chicos sovieticos
added.description: Con el fin de terminar con sus tareas domésticas y sus lecciones de karate rápidamente, los Titanes aprenden como hacer "montaje".

added.title: Pequeno Elvis
added.description: Los Titanes se unen a Shazam para derrotar al malvado Mr. Mind.

added.title: Convencion de Rath
added.description: De regreso en casa, Ben no puede inscribirse en un concurso de cosplay de gatos sin su propio disfraz. Pero cuando se convierte en Rath, un nuevo alienígena con aspecto felino y mal carácter, el lado salvaje que Ben acaba de descubrir pronto tendrá resultados inesperados.

added.title: Polos Opuestos
added.description: Un viaje al Polo Sur queda patas arriba cuando el equipo Tennyson aterriza en el Polo Norte. Pero Ben rápidamente descubre a los culpables: iSolar y Polar Twain, unos científicos con poder magnético que quieren chantajear al mundo amenazando con invertir los polos magnéticos de la Tierra!

added.title: No lo digas y Hazlo
added.description: Ben, Gwen y el Abuelo Max llegan a un parque nacional nativo americano para conocer los plintos de Ayasha, una antigua formación rocosa parecida a la de Stonehenge. Pero cuando llega el siniestro hechicero Hex, iBen debe luchar contra una bestia que Hex hizo mágicamente con rocas enormes!

added.title: Bienvenido a la Zona Zombozo
added.description: Durante tiempos medievales, el equipo Tennyson debe esforzarse por recordar que no están en el pasado, sino en una feria renacentista, idonde el "Rey Zombozo" ha hipnotizado a sus invitados para que crean que viven en el pasado!

added.title: Bloqueo de Tránsito
added.description: Cuando un paso elevado colapsa sobre la autopista, el equipo Tennyson queda varado en un embotellamiento junto con Simon Sez y familia. Pero cuando Ben y Simon se alían para enfrentar juntos al atasco, Simon solo consigue que las cosas sean mucho, pero mucho peores.

added.title: Juicio de Mino
added.description: Un grupo de Geckles creen que Kai y Zane están aliados con el Hechicero Calavera y los llevan con su líder, quien los somete a un juicio por Mino…

added.title: El Hechicero Calavera
added.description: Separado de los demás, Cole debe encontrar su camino a la superficie para advertir al Rey Vangelis sobre el peligroso Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: La Gran Caida
added.description: Este episodio relata cómo Cole, la princesa Vania y el maestro Wu caen por un túnel aparentemente interminable, dentro de la montaña de Shintaro.

added.title: Fiesta en el Calabozo
added.description: Cole, Wu y la Princesa Vania conocen a un grupo de sobrevivientes llamados los de abajo, ellos cuentan cómo terminaron en "Lo más profundo".

added.title: El Camino en el Calabozo
added.description: En su misión de derrotar al Rey Vangelis, Cole, Wu y Vania unen fuerzas con "Los de abajo" para encontrar una forma de salir del fondo de la montaña.

added.title: Ventila-hala
added.description: Chef le confisca la mega-bola a Owen y la guarda en su oficina. Duncan, viendo una oportunidad para conseguir ayuda escapando de la guardaería, lidera un equipo de fuga por los conductos del aire acondicionado para recuperarla.

added.title: Video Cita
added.description: Panda es un ávido salidor de citas por Internet, y cuando una adorable mujer francesa coincide con él y accede a tener una cita virtual con video, Panda y sus hermanos manejan la situación para poder mostrar su mejor perfil en el video, aunque ese perfil sea absolutamente exagerado.

added.title: Noticias Unikitty
added.description: Estás viendo el programa de noticias del Unireino Super Good Morning Time Action Information Show, un programa de noticias variadas realizado (mal) por Unikitty y la banda: Hawkodile se encarga del clima, Puppycorn habla deportes, a pesar de no saber ninguna de las reglas, la Dra. Fox tiene un divertido segmento de cocina científica que sale mal, y Richard quiere que el programa deje de emitirse. Unikitty tiene un reportaje contundente y una gran primicia después de la pausa, isi el estudio sobrevive tanto tiempo!

added.title: Sin Cebollin
added.description: Manzana trata de sobrevivir un fin de semana solo mientras cuida la planta de Cebollín.

added.title: Cena Festiva
added.description: Unikitty y Puppycorn están invitados al apartamento de Master Frown y Brock para una cena. Pero los dos compañeros de casa no logran ponerse de acuerdo absolutamente en nada. ¿Puede Unikitty ayudar a Brock y al Master Frown a volver a estar en armonía antes de que la cena sea un desastre? ¿Y descubrirá Puppycorn cuál es la puerta del baño?

added.title: Tienda De Mascotas
added.description: En este episodio sobre los primeros años de vida de los Osos, se cuenta la historia del lugar en el que vivieron alguna vez cuando eran bebés. Luego de un altercado con el equipo que filmaba un video absolutamente conmovedor de adopción de animales, los Osos por poco aprovechan la oportunidad de encontrar hogares alejados uno del otro.

added.title: Chloe Y Polar
added.description: Un día, Chloe sale sola a pasear con Polar y se da cuenta de que Polar se la pasa haciéndoles recados a sus hermanos. Decidida a mostrarle cómo pasarla bien en la ciudad, Chloe promete ayudar a que Polar se divierta... Aunque eso signifique quedarse dentro de un museo después de la hora de cierre.

added.title: Domingo de Flojos
added.description: Es domingo de pereza, iy Unikitty y Puppycorn la están pasando tan bien en el sofá que no quieren moverse nunca! Richard insiste en que tienen tareas por hacer, pero ellos no están dispuestos a dejar que termine el domingo de pereza. Los dos hacen todo lo posible para no salir nunca de la comodidad de su sofá, remando por el castillo como si estuvieran en un barco y reclutando a sus amigos para que abandonen sus tareas y se unan al domingo de pereza, isin importar qué tan peligroso e imposible puede llegar a ser!

added.title: Licencia para Golpear
added.description: A Hawkodile lo atrapa la policía de acción por trabajar como guardaespaldas sin licencia de acción. No puede proteger el reino ni hacer nada radical hasta tener la licencia, ipero la prueba en el Departamento de Caos y Violencia es para los nerds! Obligado a quitarse los guantes, Hawkodile lucha por vivir una vida sin golpes, por lo que Unikitty promete ayudar a su amigo a contener su impulso de entrar en acción y a estudiar para la prueba. Pero la prueba consiste en algo más de lo que parece.

added.title: La Tienda De Cupcakes
added.description: Quando o adorado computador dos ursos quebra, os três são obrigados a fazer algo que nunca haviam feito antes: arrumar um emprego. Eles começam a trabalhar numa loja badalada de cupcakes e se dão conta de que o mercado profissional é muito mais penoso do que achavam.

added.title: Manzana es Bajito
added.description: Manzana tiene que ser alto para poder enamorarse.

added.title: Bichos
added.description: Cuando Unikitty y la banda descubren un bicho asqueroso en el castillo, están desesperados por deshacerse de él para siempre, pero Unikitty se niega a permitir que lo aplasten, no importa qué tan asqueroso o peligroso parezca. ¿Qué tipo de red está tejiendo Unikitty para sus amigos?

added.title: Hibernacion
added.description: Por ser un grupo urbano, los Osos jamás escucharon hablar de la idea de hibernar, hasta que Chloe les cuenta al respecto. Pardo, a quien le encanta la idea de comer mucho y luego dormir todo lo que se le dé la gana, se entrega a la hibernación sin pensarlo. Pero está tan entusiasmado con la idea de hibernar... que no se puede dormir.

added.title: Teoria de Actitud Positiva
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín pasan un día en los zapatos de Falafel y usan su actitud positiva para demostrar que no debería estar tan malhumorado.

added.title: Revienta Fiestas
added.description: Los planes de la fiesta de Manzana y Cebollín son interrumpidos por un invitado malhumorado.

added.title: Enfrenta Tus Miedos
added.description: Atrapados en una tienda de mascotas, Manzana y Cebollín deben enfrentarse a sus miedos para poder evitar que Papa Frita se enfrente a los suyos.

added.title: Secret Origin of the Batwheels
added.description: When Batman, Robin, and Batgirl are all captured, the Batcomputer brings the Bat-Vehicles to life. Now the newly-minted Batwheels must defend the Batcave and face off with the Legion of Zoom… all without Batman's help!

added.title: Holidays on Ice
added.description: Frustrated by the Batwheels' holiday distractions, Batwing decides to "go solo" to thwart Mr. Freeze's evil Christmas-time plot. But Batwing soon realizes how hard it is to stop Mr. Freeze on her own!

added.title: Soup Up
added.description: As The Looney Builders help Petunia build a greenhouse, she can't wait for the veggies to grow and does everything she can to speed up the process.

added.title: Looneyburg Lights
added.description: The Looney Builders prepare to host a big holiday lights festival in Looneyburg Park when an unexpected snowstorm prevents Looneyburgers from attending.

added.title: Can't Stop the Martians/Best Nest Test
added.description: The Martians come to Pretty Big City but find themselves in need of help when they are unable to land their spaceship./Zee needs to communicate with Sif in outer space but can't because a bird has made its home on top of the satellite dish!

added.title: Get in Gear/Free-Wheelin' Ferris Wheel
added.description: Panic erupts in Pretty Big City when the big clock breaks and no one is able to tell what time it is./Zee is showing off his inventions at his rocket-powered show, including his latest creation, a rocket powered Ferris wheel.

added.title: Off the Rails
added.description: Nia must get a huge earth ball from Whiff's Recycling Plant to Norramby Beach, but all the rail lines are blocked! When the bouncy ball rolls off Nia's flatcar and begins a wild odyssey across Sodor, she tries to control every bounce with all her friends' help. Nia learns to roll with the bounces and calls on an unlikely hero at sea to save the cargo!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Diesel's Dilemma
added.description: When Diesel discovers that he doesn't JUST like to be known for his incredible strength, he finds an unlikely compatriot in Kenji -- who is tired of only being known for his swift speed. Diesel and Kenji decide that they are going to switch jobs for the day to show to the other engines that they're more than just their most obvious abilities. However, when both struggle in their reversed roles, Diesel and Kenji learn that it's not so bad being the strongest or the fastest... as long as you get to try new things every now and then!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Rules of the Game
added.description: When Thomas builds an obstacle course for his friends, he gets upset when they won't play with it HIS way.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: A Quiet Delivery
added.description: Thomas volunteers to get a sleeping Annie and Clarabel across Sodor without waking them up, only to discover that it's going to be harder than he imagined.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Kana Goes Slow
added.description: When Kana's power goes out during a delivery run, Thomas teaches her that sometimes it's okay to go slow.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Bats
added.description: Can you see in the dark? Blippi can't either! But on this adventure Blippi and FETCH fly around in the dark with Matt the Bat who shows them how he uses echolocation to see and hear in the dark! Who needs eyes when you can use echo-echo-echoes?

added.title: Crane
added.description: It's the first day on the job for Kareem the Crane, and he's feeling very nervous. Luckily, Blippi and FETCH are there to lend a helping hand! Working together they help Kareem to do his work. Kareem gains confidence and Blippi learns how cranes help to build a skyscraper!

added.title: Flies
added.description: Lunch is ready! Prepared to eat his delicious sandwich, Blippi notices his old friend Horace the Fly. Horace is walking upside down on the ceiling, and after shrinking down, Blippi joins him. But how does Horace stick to the ceiling? A musical song and dance from Horace is the best way to find out!

added.title: Bingo
added.description: Let's welcome our new farm friend Bingo the cat! A stray cat called Bingo is found by Ella and Mei outside of the farm. Mei calls the animal rescue center who sends Sami the Vet to check the cat over. Ella and Mei adopt Bingo and invite her to live on the farm. It is great to make new friends!

added.title: Ella Ella Yes Yes Mailman
added.description: Mailman Marcus is delivering mail to Lellobee City Farm! Ella, Rishi and Izzy are all excited to see what deliveries he has for them - Ella gets a camera, Risihi gets a ball and Izzy gets a brand new plush toy! Just as Mei thinks that she doesn't have any mail, she gets a photo delivered via drone.

added.title: Wheels on the Bus
added.description: Ella and Mummy take the big red bus to Lellobee farm, where she meets Mia and the rest of the team!

added.title: Holiday Party
added.description: "Lighting up the farm for a big 'festive' celebration Lots of lights around the farm and decorations from different cultures"

added.title: Chinese New Year
added.description: The farm is decorated for Chinese New Year. A party is taking place!

added.title: Puddle Olympics
added.description: The kids take turns jumping over a puddle but Sylvester is afraid of the water.

added.title: A Lot Like Lola
added.description: Lola wants everyone to be more like her until they all start acting exactly like her.

added.title: Mother's Day Madness
added.description: The babies compete to see who can create the best Mother's Day card.

added.title: Takers Keepers
added.description: Daffy steals Taz's favorite toy but he learns you can't just take everything you want.

added.title: To Tell the Tooth
added.description: When Bugs loses a baby tooth, Daffy tries to figure out how to scam the tooth fairy.

removed.title: T.G.I.S

removed.description: Baby Izzy doesn't like vegetables - until they sing a song with her!

removed.description: The babies experience their first snowfall.

removed.description: When Daffy starts making up hurtful rhymes, Bugs changes his name to Bruce.

removed.title: Christmas in July
removed.description: The babies pretend it's Christmas in hopes of getting Lola the stethoscope she wants.

removed.title: Spin Out
removed.description: Taz learns a tough lesson. He shouldn't spin after eating too much candy.

It's a harrowing ride, but along the way Blippi finds the answers he's looking for.

removed.title: Buff's BFF

removed.description: As the other engines prepare for a Valentine's Day party, Kana is worried: she doesn't know what to bring! Through a series of accidents, Kana realizes that the best surprise she could bring to the party is herself!

removed.description: Ella is getting muddy. Mei comes out with a plate of dumplings, but Ella's hands are dirty!
